&lt;h2&gt;We currently have vacancies&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Leominster Community Hospital&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leominster Community Hospital provides high quality patient care within a friendly team environment to a diverse client group within the GP led 26 bedded inpatient facility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work a rotational shift system to include working weekends and Bank Holidays attracting unsocial hour’s percentage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience in a similar field and an NVQ/Diploma would be an advantage, but training is encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work within a Multidisciplinary team promoting independence and patient centred care, implementing realistic individualised goals to allow proactive discharge planning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or informal visit please contact: Shirley Collin, Community Hospital Sister, on 01568 614211.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
